                "institute": "4ZZZDUB"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The beam of 6He ions was purified from",
                "both the primary beam and the main part of other react.",
                "products by using the doubly achromatic separator",
                "ACCULINNA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Secondary 24.5A MeV beam of 6He nuclei",
                "was produced by the bombardment of a 185-mg/cm2",
                "beryllium target with a 43A MeV 13C primary beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two experimental runs with CH2 targets of thicknesses",
                "of 30.1 and 53.3 mg/cm2 were carried out. These thin",
                "and thick targets were used to detect protons in the",
                "laboratory angular range of 500-700 and 400-600,",
                "respectively. For elastic scattering, these ranges",
                "correspond to the proton energies of 8-28 MeV and",
                "17-40 MeV, respectively. To see background conditions,",
                "a 44-mg/cm2 carbon target was irradiated by the",
                "6He beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector array included two",
                "position sensitive telescopes. The first telescope",
                "served as a master. It detected protons recoiled",
                "elastically or inelastically from the CH2 target.",
                "This telescope was mounted on an arm movable in the",
                "horizontal plane. The telescope consisted of two",
                "400-mu-m 60 x 60 mm2 silicon strip dE detectors and a",
                "20 mm thick 65 x 65 mm2 CsI(Tl) E detector. The",
                "overall energy resolution of the telescope was",
                "estimated to be about 2%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The RIKEN detector telescope was",
                "used to register elastically scattered 6He nuclei and",
                "alpha-particles originated from the decay of excited",
                "6He. It involved one double-side 250-mu-m silicon",
                "strip detector with both radial and annular strips",
                " (DSD), six single-side 750-mu-u silicon detectors",
                "with radial strips, and one single-side 750-mu-m",
                "silicon detector without strips."
              ]
            }
          ],
